  <h2>Access</h2>

  <h3>Repository</h3>
  <p>Use the TGS Flow GitHub repository shared in the pilot Slack channel.</p>

  <h3>Documentation</h3>
  <p>This page is the primary pilot reference.</p>
  <p>Additional resources may include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>GitHub repository README</li>
    <li>CLI documentation</li>
    <li>Pilot Slack channel</li>
  </ul>

  <hr />

  <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
  <p>Participants should have:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access to the TGS Flow GitHub repository</li>
    <li>VS Code installed if using the extension path</li>
    <li>GitHub token</li>
    <li>Jira token</li>
    <li>Jira base URL</li>
    <li>Jira project keys</li>
    <li>Access to a local repository to test the workflow</li>
    <li>A source document or meeting notes to generate backlog</li>
  </ul>

  <hr />

  <h2>Setup Instructions</h2>

  <h3>Install the VS Code Extension</h3>
  <p>Install the TGS Flow extension in VS Code.</p>

  <h3>Configure Settings</h3>
  <p>Open the Command Palette and configure:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Jira Base URL</li>
    <li>GitHub Token</li>
    <li>Jira Token</li>
    <li>Jira Project Keys</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Install Git Hooks</h3>
  <p>Run the command:</p>
  <pre>TGS Flow: Install Git Hook</pre>
  <p>This enables:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>pre commit validation</li>
    <li>post commit reconciliation</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Confirm Commands</h3>
  <p>Verify the following commands are available:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Install Git Hook</li>
    <li>Reconcile Work</li>
    <li>Scan TODOs to Jira</li>
    <li>Solution Doc to Backlog</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Run Initial Test</h3>
  <p>Use a sample document or notes to confirm the workflow works.</p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Core Workflow</h2>

  <h3>Primary Use Case</h3>
  <p>Typical workflow:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Team holds a design or planning session</li>
    <li>Notes or a solution document are created</li>
    <li>The document is used to generate Jira backlog items</li>
    <li>Backlog is reviewed and refined in Jira</li>
    <li>Work is assigned to engineers</li>
    <li>Engineers begin implementation</li>
    <li>GitHub commits update Jira automatically</li>
    <li>Jira reflects real execution</li>
  </ol>

  <hr />

  <h2>Key Commands</h2>

  <h3>Install Git Hook</h3>
  <p>Installs repository hooks enabling automated validation and reconciliation.</p>

  <h3>Reconcile Work</h3>
  <p>Manually scans commits and reconciles them with Jira issues.</p>

  <h3>Scan TODOs to Jira</h3>
  <p>Finds TODO comments in code and proposes Jira issues.</p>

  <h3>Solution Doc to Backlog</h3>
  <p>Generates candidate backlog items from a solution document.</p>

  <hr />

